Been here a few times when visiting Vegas and thought I should give them some justice consider the price I'm paying against the atmosphere, service, and food quality.
You can't compare this to a $40+ buffet on the strip that's for sure, but whenever I'm on a business travel in the area and want some asian buffet, this is where I go to without breaking the bank.
Service is very friendly and courteous.
Receptionist is informative and staff is quick consider the size of the place.
Offer to help you get drinks even when the soda machine is right outside.
I know some other buffets charges you extra if you want to get things other than tap water.
Food is not luxurious, but you get way more than what you've paid for.
They listen to your opinions, and change their menu quite frequently.
Lots of local asian dishes, ducks, pork, chicken, veggies, and oh oh I love their plain radish soup.
Looks plain but full of flavor!
Many great pork selections.
They also have a few American food that's just there to diversify I guess (but their onion ring is not bad).
The interior design is more than pleasing the eyes.
Outside looks normal, but once you step in to the restaurant you will be pleased to see they actually spent quite some $$ to decorate this place, yet still offering value meals.
Check out their bathroom too!
On the side there looks like an area for group to host parties or something.
Might be good to ask.
Bummer they only open for lunch hours, and I came once around 2pm their food almost ran out.
Gave me a discount and even cook additional food just for me to make sure I get my money well spent.
With that, I believe it definitely deserves a 5 star.
You might be fooled by its fancy design thinking it is a high end buffet, and gave it a 1 star because their food is not $40 worth, but you are NOT paying $40+.
So, here I am making justice.
:)  Keep it going!!
and offer dinner~ or hotpot, or something interesting!

